@mioteks, burn the ISO to a disc by right clicking it on a Windows 7 computer and select Open with Windows Disc Image Burner. If you don't have a Windows 7 computer yet, use the free Microsoft's USB/DVD Download Tool (google it) so you can transfer it to either a DVD or a thumb drive. Alternatively, you can transfer it to a thumb drive using the free Universal USB Installer or the YUMI which can be found at pendrivelinux.com.

After preparing the thumb drive, boot from it and follow the menu. When done installing, run the Windows Loader to activate it if it isn't activated yet.

